Introduction

Youngjae is a South Korean singer-songwriter, composer, and actor under AndBut Company. He is best known as the main vocalist of GOT7, debuting with the group on January 16, 2014, with the single "Girls Girls Girls."

Following the expiration of his contract with JYP Entertainment in 2021, Youngjae signed with Sublime Artist Agency on January 20. He made his solo debut on October 5, 2021, with the EP "Colors from Ars" and its title track "Vibin." On April 2, 2024, he mutually parted ways with Sublime, later signing an exclusive contract with AndBut Company on June 24, 2024.
